excerpt: Shiva temple built by the Indian Army, known for its aluminum-covered geodesic dome construction.
detail_description: The EME Temple in Vadodara is a unique blend of modern architecture and ancient sculpture, dedicated to Lord Shiva. Constructed by the Indian Army, this contemporary temple features a geodesic dome covered with aluminum sheets, designed by renowned architect Gerard da Cunha. It has been under construction for over 25 years and incorporates aspects of major Indian religions.
name: EME Temple
address: 85JR+GPV, nr. EME TEMPLE, Fatehgunj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390002, India

excerpt: Large, imposing monument building with murals & busts, site of occasional photo & art exhibitions.
detail_description: Nestled across the Vishwamitra River and just a short stroll from Sayaji Baug, Kirti Mandir stands as an impressive tribute to the Gaekwad dynasty in Vadodara. This magnificent temple, dedicated to Lord Shiva, was constructed in 1936 to honor Maharaja Sayajirao Gaekwad III's Diamond Jubilee.
name: Kirti Mandir
address: Kothi Rd, Dak Bunglaw, Sayajiganj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

excerpt: Massive, 19th-century palace in landscaped surrounds featuring an art museum, concert hall & zoo.
detail_description: Lukshmi Vilas Palace is a grand 19th-century palace surrounded by beautiful gardens and home to an art museum, concert hall, and zoo. Commissioned in 1890 by Maharaja Sayajirao Gaekwad III, the palace was designed by Charles Mant and Robert Chisholm, known for their Indo-Saracenic architecture that blends European and South Asian styles. The sprawling palace is adorned with bronze sculptures by Italian artist Fellici Casorati.
name: Laxshmi Vilas Palace
address: J N Marg, Moti Baug, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

detail_description: Sayaji Baug, often referred to as Kamati Baug, is a stunning public garden located in Vadodara and is recognized as one of the largest gardens in India, covering an impressive 100 acres. This lush oasis boasts around 98 species of trees and a rich variety of flora, making it a paradise for nature lovers. Visitors can marvel at the largest floral clock in India while enjoying the serene surroundings.
name: Sayaji Baug
address: 857R+835, Dak Bunglaw, Sayajiganj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

excerpt: Century-old museum & gallery displaying Asian & Middle Eastern paintings, sculptures & weaponry.
detail_description: Baroda Museum & Picture Gallery, located within Sayaji Bagh, is a century-old museum and gallery displaying Asian and Middle Eastern paintings, sculptures, and weaponry. The museum features an extensive collection of artifacts related to archaeology, geology, natural history, personal collections of Maharaja Sayajirao III, and 109 miniature paintings from the Mughal era. The two-storied buildings are built in the Indo-Saracenic style of architecture.
name: Baroda Museum & Picture Gallery
address: Kamatibaug, Dak Bunglaw, Sayajiganj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390020, India

excerpt: Boasting a 120-ft.-tall statue in the middle, this central urban lake is a popular gathering spot.
detail_description: Sur Sagar Lake, also known as Chand Talao, is a prominent urban lake located in the heart of Vadodara. The largest artificial lake in the city, it was built with water conservation in mind. The 120-ft.-tall Shiva statue at its center makes it a popular gathering spot for couples, families, and visitors. Surrounded by lush greenery, the lake offers boat rides for a relaxing evening experience.
name: Sur Sagar Lake
address: Vadodara, Gujarat 390001

detail_description: Tambekar Wada is a 19th-century Maratha mansion in Vadodara, once the residence of Bhau Tambekar, the Diwan of Baroda state. Despite its derelict exterior, the interior is a mesmerizing display of Maratha architecture.
name: Tambekar Wada
address: 853X+4M6, Dandia Bazar, Jambubet, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

detail_description: Nestled in the serene city of Vadodara, Sri Aurobindo Ashram stands as a tranquil retreat that invites visitors to step away from the hustle and bustle of daily life. This historic site was home to Aurobindo Ghosh during his influential years from 1894 to 1906, where he made significant contributions as a philosopher and yogi.
name: Sri Aurobindo Ashram
address: 852W+6C2, Jambubet Rd, Dandia Bazar, Jambubet, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

excerpt: Founded in 1961, this museum in a royal palace houses Rococo paintings, sculptures & artifacts.
detail_description: The Maharaja Fateh Singh Museum is located within the lavish Lakshmi Vilas Palace complex in Vadodara, Gujarat. Originally built as a school for the royal family, this museum showcases Rococo paintings, sculptures, and personal belongings of the Gaekwad family. The palace itself is an architectural marvel blending European and South Asian styles and features bronze sculptures by Fellici Casorati.
name: Maharaja Fateh Singh Museum
address: Jawaharlal Nehru Marg, Navapura, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

excerpt: Sprawling park featuring a museum, a planetarium, a zoo & a small train in a garden setting.
detail_description: Sayaji Baug Zoo is a part of the sprawling Sayaji Baug, a park that offers a variety of attractions including a museum, planetarium, and a small train. The zoo, nestled in this 113-acre park founded in 1879 by Maharaja Sayajirao III, provides an opportunity to connect with nature amidst serene surroundings along the Vishwamitri River. The zoo is home to exotic birds and playful mammals, making it an ideal place for wildlife enthusiasts.
name: Sayaji Baug Zoo
address: Vinoba Bhave Rd, Near Kala Ghoda, Dak Bunglaw, Sayajiganj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390005, India

detail_description: Maharaja Sayajirao University, formerly known as Vadodara College, is a renowned educational institution in Vadodara, India. Established in 1881 and renamed in 1949 to honor Maharaja Sayajirao Gaekwad III, the university offers various faculties including arts, sciences, management studies, medicine, and pharmacy.
name: Maharaja Sayajirao University
address: Sayajiganj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390020, India

excerpt: 200-seat planetarium offering shows in English, Gujarati & Hindi focusing on astronomical history.
detail_description: Located in the scenic Sayaji Baug, Sardar Patel Planetarium is a must-visit destination in Vadodara. With a 200-seat capacity, this planetarium offers captivating shows in English, Gujarati, and Hindi that delve into the history of astronomy. Equipped with advanced projection technology and a dome-shaped screen, it brings the wonders of celestial bodies to life. The planetarium runs hourly shows every evening except Thursdays and also arranges special educational shows upon request.
name: Sardar Patel Planetarium
address: Gate No. 1, Kala Ghoda Cir, Dak Bunglaw, Sayaji Baug, Vadodara, Gujarat 390005, India

detail_description: Vadodara Railway Station, the 9th busiest in India and the most bustling in Gujarat, sees a significant amount of train activity. With a total of 360 trains passing through, including 170 major ones originating, terminating, or crossing at this station, it serves as a crucial hub for rail transportation in the region.
name: Vadodara Railway Station
address: Maharaja Sayajirao University, Sayajiganj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390005, India

detail_description: The Nandalay Temple in Vadodara is one of the most popular Hindu temples in the city. The temple is dedicated to Lord Krishna, and it is said that devotees are always blessed by Him. The temple also features a beautiful Rajbhog Prasadi, or offering ceremony, which is a great opportunity to get close to Lord Krishna.
name: Nandalay Temple
address: 8572+GX5, Rajesh Tower Rd, Divya Darshan Society, Gotri, Vadodara, Gujarat 390021, India

detail_description: Sayaji Garden, also known as Kamati Baug, is a picturesque oasis that invites visitors to unwind amidst its lush greenery and vibrant floral displays. This expansive garden features serene lakes and even houses a zoo where you can observe various animal species. It's an ideal spot for jogging, walking, or simply enjoying morning strolls in a peaceful atmosphere. The tranquil setting makes it perfect for yoga enthusiasts seeking mindfulness and relaxation while connecting with nature.
name: Sayaji Garden
address: 63QQ+8R8, MS University, Padra, Gujarat 391440, India

excerpt: This 16th-century city gate adorned with arches is a popular place for vendors to sell their wares.
detail_description: Mandvi Gate is a significant historical site in Vadodara, dating back to the 16th century. It is a square-shaped pavilion with three arched openings on each side and was once used as a toll gate for traders and merchants. The city's original walls may have vanished, but Mandvi Gate still stands as one of the four imposing gates, reflecting a blend of Islamic and Maratha architecture.
name: Mandvi Gate
address: Mandvi Cir, Sulemani Pol, Mandvi, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

excerpt: Clothing & food stalls occupy the garden of this landmark from 1906, popular for street photography.
detail_description: Khanderao Market Building, a landmark from 1906 in Vadodara city, Gujarat, is a bustling hub with clothing and food stalls set up in its garden. The market is popular for street photography and is one of the iconic landmarks of the city. It's part of a list of tourist attractions that draw visitors from around the world to Vadodara. The building was designed by Chisholm, who also worked on other significant structures in India during his time there.
name: Khanderao Market Building
address: 76W2+MGX, Kevdabaug, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

excerpt: This large tower made of pink stone was built in 1935 & features a lion statue at the top.
detail_description: Kirti Stambh, a prominent landmark in Vadodara, is a towering structure made of pink Songadh stone that was constructed in 1935 to honor Maharaja Sayajirao Gaekwad III's 60-year reign. The stambh features a lion statue at its pinnacle and offers panoramic views of the city. It is a popular spot for visitors to enjoy sunset picnics and marvel at the architectural grandeur.
name: Kirti Stambh
address: Kirti stambh circle, Palace Rd, Vadodara, Gujarat 390001, India

name: Shree Swaminarayan Temple  Karelibaug, Vadodara
address: Pani Tanki Rd, Karelibagh, Vadodara, Gujarat 390018, India

detail_description: The Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda, commonly known as MSU, is a prestigious institution established in 1881 under the vision of Maharaja Sayajirao Gaekwad III. Located in Vadodara, it is a popular tourist attraction due to its rich history and architectural significance. The university's campus includes notable landmarks such as the Lakshmi Vilas Palace and Baroda Museum.
name: The Maharaja Sayajirao University of Baroda
address: Pratapgunj, Vadodara, Gujarat 390002, India
